       title="Uploading files" id="Uploading-files">

    <note>If you use the desktop app, all operations will still be local on your own computer. No data is transferred to a remote server. The upload/download terminology
    comes from how J-AST works internally and how it manages data.</note>
    <p>After creating the project, you can upload your image files. We currently support all standard image files supported by Java, including PNG and JPEG.
    We recommend to use PNG due to the lossless compression.</p>
    <p>To open the uploader, click the <ui-path>UPLOAD</ui-path> button located on the left-hand side in the toolbar. This will open a new panel where
    you can add files to upload through clicking the <ui-path>âž•</ui-path> button.</p>
    <img src="jast-uploader.png" alt="Uploader panel"/>
    Finally, click the <ui-path>UPLOAD NOW</ui-path> button to start uploading the data into J-AST.
    After uploading your data, you can close the upload panel by clicking the <ui-path>UPLOAD</ui-path> button again.
